parks.name: Maasai Mara National Reserve
parks.description: Famous for its incredible wildlife, including the Big Five and the Great Migration. A must-visit for safari enthusiasts.

parks.name: Amboseli National Park
parks.description: Known for its large elephant herds and stunning views of Mount Kilimanjaro. Offers excellent opportunities for wildlife photography.
parks.address: Amboseli National Park, Kajiado County, Kenya

parks.name: Tsavo National Park
parks.description: The largest national park in Kenya, home to a wide variety of wildlife, including lions, elephants, and giraffes. Offers excellent opportunities for game viewing and camping.

parks.name: Lake Nakuru National Park
parks.description: Home to a large population of flamingos, as well as other wildlife such as lions, leopards, and buffaloes. Offers excellent opportunities for birdwatching and game viewing.
parks.address: Lake Nakuru National Park, Nakuru County, Kenya

parks.name: Ol Pejeta Conservancy
parks.description: Home to the only black rhinos in Kenya, as well as other wildlife such as lions, leopards, and elephants. Offers excellent opportunities for wildlife viewing and conservation education.
